The Cape Town Weather Office says a weak cold front is moving across the south-western part of the Western Cape on Thursday, bringing light rain from overnight to Friday morning. Forecaster, Matshidiso Mogale, says it will start clearing up by Friday afternoon but another cold front is expected to move in on Saturday. “It will move through the south-western parts from the afternoon resulting in some light rains over the Cape Peninsula area, spreading over the Metropole towards the evening and over along the South Coast overnight into Sunday morning. Sunday it will remain partly cloudy, no further rain will be expected.” 